  </div>
</section>

<!-- FORMAT -->
<section class="format-section" id="format">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-label fade-up">The format</div>
    <h2 class="section-title fade-up">10 hours of focused building.</h2>
    <p class="section-sub fade-up">No slides. No pitch decks at the start. You arrive, you form a team, you build. At the end, you demo a working product to the investors in the room.</p>

    <div class="timeline fade-up">
      <div class="timeline-item">
        <div class="timeline-time">10:00</div>
        <div class="timeline-dot"><div class="timeline-dot-circle"></div><div class="timeline-dot-line"></div></div>
        <div class="timeline-content">
          <h3>Kickoff &amp; theme reveal</h3>
          <p>The technical theme or problem space is announced. Team up, pick your angle, define your scope. You have 30 minutes to align — then you build.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="timeline-item">
        <div class="timeline-time">10:30</div>
        <div class="timeline-dot"><div class="timeline-dot-circle"></div><div class="timeline-dot-line"></div></div>
        <div class="timeline-content">
          <h3>Building begins</h3>
          <p>Heads down. Real code, real infrastructure, real product. Experienced mentors are in the room to unblock you when you're stuck.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="timeline-item">
        <div class="timeline-time">13:00</div>
        <div class="timeline-dot"><div class="timeline-dot-circle"></div><div class="timeline-dot-line"></div></div>
        <div class="timeline-content">
          <h3>Lunch + mid-day check-in</h3>
          <p>Break, eat, recalibrate. Optional 5-minute mid-day check-ins with a mentor if you've hit a wall or want to pressure-test your approach.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="timeline-item">
        <div class="timeline-time">14:00</div>
        <div class="timeline-dot"><div class="timeline-dot-circle"></div><div class="timeline-dot-line"></div></div>
        <div class="timeline-content">
          <h3>Back to building</h3>
          <p>Afternoon block. Focus on making it work end-to-end, not just look good. A working demo matters more than a polished UI.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="timeline-item">
        <div class="timeline-time">18:00</div>
        <div class="timeline-dot"><div class="timeline-dot-circle"></div><div class="timeline-dot-line"></div></div>
        <div class="timeline-content">
          <h3>Freeze + prep demos</h3>
          <p>Code freeze. Two hours to prep your demo — no new features, just make it presentable and tell the story clearly.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="timeline-item">
        <div class="timeline-time">19:00</div>
        <div class="timeline-dot"><div class="timeline-dot-circle"></div><div class="timeline-dot-line"></div></div>
        <div class="timeline-content">
          <h3>Demo + pitches</h3>
          <p>Each team gets 5 minutes. Live demo, one slide max. Mentors and peers ask real questions. The best teams get follow-up conversations, not just a prize.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="timeline-item">
        <div class="timeline-time">20:00</div>
        <div class="timeline-dot"><div class="timeline-dot-circle"></div><div class="timeline-dot-line"></div></div>
        <div class="timeline-content">
          <h3>Awards + networking</h3>
          <p>Prizes, credits, and introductions. More importantly: the people in this room are who you want to know.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- WHO ATTENDS -->
<section>
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-label fade-up">Who attends</div>
    <h2 class="section-title fade-up">Built for people who ship.</h2>
    <p class="section-sub fade-up">This isn't a general hackathon. We select for technical ability and the drive to build real things — not to win competitions.</p>

    <div class="who-grid">
      <div class="who-card fade-up">
        <div class="who-card-icon">⚡</div>
        <h3>Technical founders</h3>
        <p>You've already shipped something. You build fast. You want a focused day with peers at your level and direct access to investors who get technical products.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="who-card fade-up">
        <div class="who-card-icon">🛠</div>
        <h3>Developers exploring startups</h3>
        <p>You're a strong engineer who's been thinking about building your own thing. This is a low-stakes way to test if you like the founder experience.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="who-card fade-up">
        <div class="who-card-icon">🎓</div>
        <h3>CS &amp; engineering students</h3>
        <p>From KU Leuven, UGent, VUB, or elsewhere. You want to build something real, meet people who are doing it, and get in front of investors early.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>



<!-- WHAT YOU BUILD -->
<section>
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-label fade-up">What you walk away with</div>
    <h2 class="section-title fade-up">More than a weekend project.</h2>
    <p class="section-sub fade-up">The goal isn't to win a hackathon. The goal is to leave with something worth continuing — and people worth building with.</p>

    <div class="output-grid">
      <div class="output-item fade-up">
        <div class="output-accent" style="background:var(--accent)"></div>
        <h3>A working technical demo</h3>
        <p>Not a mockup. Not a pitch deck. A live product that does something real — and that you built under pressure in 8 hours.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="output-item fade-up">
        <div class="output-accent" style="background:var(--teal)"></div>
        <h3>Meaningful introductions</h3>
        <p>Experienced founders and builders are in the room all day. If your build gets their attention, the conversation starts that evening — not 6 months later.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="output-item fade-up">
        <div class="output-accent" style="background:var(--purple)"></div>
        <h3>Your co-founder, maybe</h3>
        <p>Teams form on the day. Some of the best founder partnerships start at events like this. You won't know until you build together.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

